# Python style

## Required

- `from __future__ import annotations` at the top of every `.py` file (except `__init__.py`).
- `logging.getLogger(__name__)` instead of `print`. Never log tokens.
- Dataclasses — `@dataclass(frozen=True)` for config / value objects.
- Type annotations: `list[X]`, `dict[str, X]`, `str | None` (PEP 604). Python 3.13 applies.
- Docstrings in English, ASCII-safe (match the rest of the codebase).
- File names — `snake_case`; classes — `PascalCase`; constants — `UPPER_SNAKE`.

## Errors / exceptions

- Network / Playwright / GitHub errors — catch `Exception`, log with `logger.exception(...)`, continue the cycle.
- Introduce domain errors (`SearchError` already exists) only when the caller has something different to do.

## Don't

```python
# BAD
try:
    run_cycle(settings)
except Exception:
    pass   # error swallowed

# BAD
logger.info(f"token={settings.github_token}")  # secret leak

# BAD
from requests import get   # don't pull in requests; use urllib
```

## Do

```python
# GOOD
try:
    run_cycle(settings)
except Exception:
    logger.exception("run_cycle failed")

# GOOD
logger.info("GitHub push OK sha=%s", commit.get("sha", "?")[:7])

# GOOD
import urllib.request
req = urllib.request.Request(url, data=data, method="PUT")
```

## Formatting

- No black/ruff config — follow existing style (4 spaces, ~95 col max).
- Import order: stdlib -> third-party -> `.relative`. Alphabetical within a group.
- No `# type: ignore` without a comment explaining why.
